properties.Name: ExperianJudgment
properties.Description:
Judgment flings are court decisions directing a business (who are the defendant) to make payments to a plaintiff. 

Judgments are therefore debts that can be an indication of trouble. 

All Fling types are counted (including vacated judgments and releases), and retained for six years and nine months.

Columns.Name: ExperianFileNumber
Columns.Description: The unique and persistent number that identifies and tracks the Experian company.

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp of the Experian profile.

Columns.Name: PlaintiffName
Columns.Description: The name of the plaintiff to the judgment.

Columns.Name: ExperianJudgmentFilingTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Experian judgment filing type.

Columns.Name: ExperianJudgmentStatusTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Experian judgment status type.
